<subSubSection pageId="106" pageNumber="107" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="106.[189,400,569,595]" box="[189,400,569,595]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,400,569,595]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,400,569,595]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Brief description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="106.[189,1398,616,714]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Monoecious. Receptacle consisting of 6–8 cells viz.: a basal cell (I), 2–4 cells Ia, two cells II, and one cell III. Cell III subtends two broad cells which each bear two bell-shaped antheridia. The perithecium has two adjacent vertical rows of outer wall cells with 4–5 cells, and other two rows with 7–8 cells.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="106" pageNumber="107" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="106.[189,303,753,779]" box="[189,303,753,779]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
